    <shortFormBody xml:space="preserve" xml:base="http://www.bbc.co.uk/article/5bdf78a1-58df-2d4d-b400-7269adf49f20">
    	<paragraph>Google has started uploading the latest version of its Android system to users' smartphones. </paragraph>
    	<paragraph>Owners of the HSPA+ version of Samsung's Galaxy Nexus - available in the UK, most of Europe and the US - are the first to receive the update. </paragraph>
    	<paragraph>Google says the Jelly Bean software offers an improved search experience. </paragraph>
    	<paragraph>But it does not appear to have amended the system to take account of a patent row that briefly caused the Nexus phone to be banned from sale in the US. </paragraph>
    </shortFormBody>  
